Here’s the relevant area:

```
[2019-09-16 00:42] [INFO] glutin event: NewEvents(WaitCancelled { start: Instant { t: 270664.5210621s }, requested_resume: None })
[2019-09-16 00:42] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(WindowId(0x1e05e2)), event: KeyboardInput { device_id: DeviceId(DeviceId(0)), input: KeyboardInput { scancode: 0, state: Pressed, virtual_keycode: None, modifiers: ModifiersState { shift: true, ctrl: false, alt: false, logo: false } } } }
[2019-09-16 00:42] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(WindowId(0x1e05e2)), event: ReceivedCharacter('\u{d83d}') }
[2019-09-16 00:42] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(WindowId(0x1e05e2)), event: KeyboardInput { device_id: DeviceId(DeviceId(0)), input: KeyboardInput { scancode: 0, state: Released, virtual_keycode: None, modifiers: ModifiersState { shift: true, ctrl: false, alt: false, logo: false } } } }
[2019-09-16 00:42] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(WindowId(0x1e05e2)), event: KeyboardInput { device_id: DeviceId(DeviceId(0)), input: KeyboardInput { scancode: 0, state: Pressed, virtual_keycode: None, modifiers: ModifiersState { shift: true, ctrl: false, alt: false, logo: false } } } }
[2019-09-16 00:42] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(WindowId(0x1e05e2)), event: ReceivedCharacter('\u{de00}') }
[2019-09-16 00:42] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(WindowId(0x1e05e2)), event: KeyboardInput { device_id: DeviceId(DeviceId(0)), input: KeyboardInput { scancode: 0, state: Released, virtual_keycode: None, modifiers: ModifiersState { shift: true, ctrl: false, alt: false, logo: false } } } }
[2019-09-16 00:42] [INFO] glutin event: EventsCleared
```

It’s the usual surrogate situation, with the character coming through in two UTF-16 code unit events, and whatever’s slurping them isn’t gluing them back together. I’ve helped get such bugs fixed several times. (Vim is the main one I remember, in https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/2800.) Gotta say that I think Glutin is probably the right place for this rather than here.
